line=3 fonts=F1-16.0 bbox=56.7,639.8,152.17,655.82                                :1. Introduction
line=4 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,617.42,538.55,631.4 iscore=0.08                    :Predicates can have one or more arguments. For nouns, one  can distinguish between
line=5 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,601.34,538.67,615.32 iscore=0.21           :absolute nouns such  as tree or stick, which have a single argument, and relational
line=6 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,585.2,538.62,599.18 iscore=0.29            :nouns such  as head and father, which have two  arguments that are strictly ordered:
line=7 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,569.12,538.68,583.1 iscore=0.29            :head refers to the head of someone, and it is this lower argument that can be realized
line=8 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,553.04,538.56,567.02 iscore=0.24                   :by an inalienable possessor. Moreover, most absolute nouns can undergo a possessor
line=9 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,536.9,538.66,550.88 iscore=0.23                    :extension, as shown in (1c), thus becoming relational with an alienable possessor as
line=10 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,519.8,538.63,533.78 iscore=0.31                   :the lower argument. In the notation used here, a sequence of λ-abstractors precedes
line=11 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,503.66,538.63,517.64 iscore=0.31                  :the open proposition which  is formed by the predicate and the argument  variables,
line=12 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,487.58,538.68,501.56 iscore=0.29                  :and it reflects the ordering of arguments: the lower argument role is to the left and the
line=13 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,471.5,538.55,485.48 iscore=0.24                   :higher argument role to the right. Note that the higher argument of a noun is a refer-
line=14 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,455.36,538.57,469.34 iscore=0.29                  :ential argument, which is realized as a complement only in predicative use; otherwise
line=15 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,439.28,424.08,453.26 iscore=0.08                  :it is bound by functional categories such as articles or quantifiers.
line=16 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,417.2,219.89,431.18 iscore=0.09                   :(1)   Classification of nouns
line=17 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0,F3-14.0 bbox=90.72,400.03,271.71,414.02 iscore=0.25 :      a. absolute:        λx TREE(x)
line=18 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0,F3-14.0 bbox=209.68,382.87,275.97,396.86 iscore=1.00:                          λx STICK(x)
