line=45 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,660.44,538.62,674.42                      :Relational verbs can also be telic (such as kill) or atelic (such as to boil something), a
line=46 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,644.36,538.62,658.34 iscore=0.18                  :property which  is mostly determined with respect to the lower argument.  In (3b),
line=47 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,628.28,538.58,642.26 iscore=0.14                  :these verbs are decomposed,  and  the inherent aspect is a property of the second
line=48 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,612.13,538.64,626.12 iscore=0.20          :predicate; the predicate ACT, which is taken as the first predicate, is a general atelic
line=49 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,596.06,538.61,610.04 iscore=0.27                  :activity predicate. Canonical transitive verbs have a patient (which is affected by the
line=50 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,579.98,538.59,593.96 iscore=0.08                  :event) and an agent (which controls the event); thus, the inherent control properties
line=51 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,563.84,538.6,577.82 iscore=0.15                   :are distributed among the two  predicates in (3b). There are other transitive verbs
line=52 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,547.76,538.63,561.74 iscore=0.07          :(such as hit) that cannot as easily be decomposed into two predicates, but neverthe-
line=53 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,531.68,279.46,545.66 iscore=0.21                  :less show the same semantic properties.
line=54 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,509.54,273.07,523.52 iscore=0.33                  :(3)   Classification of relational verbs
line=55 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=90.71,493.46,153.96,507.44 iscore=0.25                 :      a. static (t)
line=56 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0,F3-14.0 bbox=107.7,476.35,259.61,490.34 iscore=0.25 :         λy λx λt SURROUND(x,y)(t)
