line=128 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,608.9,538.55,622.88             :Six different types of argument linking will be discussed. The active type mainly uses
line=129 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,591.86,538.63,605.84 iscore=0.14:semantic role, while the salience type uses salience. The positional type realizes ar-
line=130 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,574.88,538.65,588.86 iscore=0.31:gument  hierarchy in the syntax. The inverse type maps salience hierarchy onto argu-
line=131 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,557.9,538.62,571.88 iscore=0.23 :ment hierarchy. The generalized case type introduces structural case, but can also use
line=132 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,540.86,538.62,554.84 iscore=0.15:salience (split systems) and semantic roles (lexical case). The portmanteau type sim-
line=133 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,523.88,538.61,537.86 iscore=0.21:ply lists the possible combinations of argument features. Some of these types can be
line=134 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,506.9,229.31,520.88 iscore=0.07 :mixed in individual languages.

doc_id=101 page=4 block_id=4-5 bbox=56.7,125.3,538.65,493.88 label=tbbb 135 155
line=135 fonts=F1-14.0,F1-16.0 bbox=56.7,477.86,538.59,493.88           :2.1.  Portmanteau   type: Affixes on the verb specify more than one argument si-
line=136 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,460.88,538.58,474.86 iscore=0.31       :multaneously. Single portmanteau affixes can be found in many languages, as the ex-
line=137 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,443.9,538.62,457.88 iscore=0.27        :amples in (7) illustrate. The notation ‘A→B’ means that the form specifies A for the
line=138 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,426.86,538.5,440.84 iscore=0.33        :higher argument and B for the lower argument of a transitive verb, for example, the
line=139 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,409.88,468.8,423.86 iscore=0.27:Hungarian suffix -lak/-lek is used with 1sg subject and 2nd person object.
line=140 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,388.52,248.96,402.5 iscore=0.08        :(7)   Single portmanteau-suffixes
line=141 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=95.64,371.12,396.09,386.12 iscore=0.33      :      Hungarian                        -lak/-lek 1sg→2
line=142 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=95.64,353.48,389.85,368.48 iscore=0.17      :      Ayacucho  and Cuzco Quechua        -yki     1→2
line=143 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=95.64,335.78,396.09,350.78 iscore=0.29      :      Dumi  (Kiranti language in Nepal)   -n     1sg→2
line=144 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=95.64,318.68,396.09,334.7 iscore=0.43       :      [van Driem 1993]                    -u     1sg→3
line=145 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,295.28,538.54,309.26 iscore=0.00       :It is quite rare that pronominal affixes in general are of the portmanteau type. One
line=146 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,278.3,538.64,292.28 iscore=0.13        :can easily see that this way of argument marking is rather uneconomical because the
line=147 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,261.26,538.63,275.24 iscore=0.14       :speakers have to memorize a large number of morphological items, and it is difficult
line=148 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,244.28,538.65,258.26 iscore=0.14       :to make any generalizations. One example is Kiowa, spoken in the Tanoan pueblos of
line=149 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,227.3,538.57,241.28 iscore=0.14        :New  Mexico  and Arizona, illustrated by a few examples in (8). Watkins (1984) tries
line=150 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,210.26,538.59,224.24 iscore=0.21       :to derive the prefix forms from more minimal underlying features, however, the rules
line=151 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,193.28,538.65,207.26 iscore=0.21       :and exceptions he states are quite numerous, so that it is questionable whether such
line=152 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,176.3,538.65,190.28 iscore=0.21        :an analysis meets what speakers really know about their language. I simply assume
line=153 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,159.26,538.65,173.24 iscore=0.08       :here that they have memorized the prefixes with portmanteau information, which in
line=154 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,142.28,538.6,156.26 iscore=0.23        :fact is often very complex, including alternative specifications for either the higher or
line=155 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,125.3,168.89,139.28 iscore=0.08        :the lower argument.

doc_id=101 page=4 block_id=4-6 bbox=56.7,59.29,538.67,101.48 label=b 156 158
line=156 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-9.0 bbox=56.7,85.99,538.67,101.48           :1 Some  predicates already determine a certain sortal selection for their arguments, for instance, the higher
line=157 fonts=F1-11.0,F2-11.0 bbox=56.7,72.31,538.62,83.3 iscore=0.17:argument  of see must be animate, while the lower argument of cut must be inanimate. Hence, predicates of
