doc_id=101 page=6 block_id=6-2 bbox=56.7,101.54,538.69,772.22 label=b 198 237
line=198 fonts=F1-14.0,F1-16.0 bbox=56.7,756.2,538.63,772.22                                                                              :2.3 Salience  type: Affixes on the verb specify the more salient argument; some af-
line=199 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,739.82,538.59,753.8 iscore=0.13                                                                          :fixes also specify whether a more salient argument is added to the verb. The exam-
line=200 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,723.68,538.64,737.66 iscore=0.20                                                                         :ples are taken from  Arizona Tewa,  another Tanoan   language, which, however,  is
line=201 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,707.6,538.57,721.58 iscore=0.31                                                                          :quite different from Kiowa in the way arguments are specified. Arizona Tewa exhib-
line=202 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,691.52,538.57,705.5 iscore=0.18                                                                          :its six distinct sets of person prefixes, listed in (11), but only one prefix is possible at
line=203 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,675.38,395.35,689.36 iscore=0.24                                                                         :a time. It is always the most salient argument that is marked.
line=204 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,658.58,538.51,672.56 iscore=0.00                                                                        :   Intransitive verbs only have one argument, marked by  a stative prefix, but if the
line=205 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,641.6,538.61,655.58 iscore=0.31                                                                          :argument  has a possessor, the latter counts as more salient and is marked by a sepa-
line=206 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,624.56,538.58,638.54 iscore=0.25                                                                         :rate prefix. With transitive verbs, prefixes from four different sets are possible.
line=207 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,607.58,538.57,621.56 iscore=0.13                                                                         :Agents  are marked if they are more salient than the patient (3rd person), while pa-
line=208 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,590.6,538.58,604.58 iscore=0.31                                                                          :tients are marked (in particular those being 1st or 2nd person) if they are more salient
line=209 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,573.56,538.67,587.54 iscore=0.25                                                                         :than the agent; in the latter case, the less salient syntactic argument must be marked
line=210 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,556.57,538.61,570.56 iscore=0.20                                                                 :oblique. Thus, the direct and the inverse setting are distinguished by AGT vs. PAT
line=211 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,539.6,538.63,553.58 iscore=0.38                                                                          :marking, in this respect the salience type is similar to the active type. For reflexives, a
line=212 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,522.56,538.61,536.54 iscore=0.38                                                                         :separate marker exists. Finally, if a beneficiary is introduced, it counts as the most
line=213 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,505.58,355.47,519.56 iscore=0.07                                                                         :salient argument, and only this argument is specified.
line=214 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,484.22,441.61,498.2 iscore=0.18                                                                          :(11)  Arizona Tewa: the six sets of person prefixes [Kroskrity 1985]
line=215 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,468.43,265.93,482.42 iscore=0.20                                                                :      a. STAT with intransitive verbs
line=216 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,452.41,264.73,466.4 iscore=1.00                                                                 :      b. POSS with intransitive verbs
line=217 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,436.39,250.09,450.38 iscore=0.40                                                                :      c. AGT with transitive verbs
line=218 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,420.43,248.29,434.42 iscore=0.80                                                                :      d. PAT with transitive verbs
line=219 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,404.41,254.41,418.4 iscore=0.40                                                                 :      e. REFL with transitive verbs
line=220 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,388.39,249.49,402.38 iscore=0.60                                                                :      f. BEN with transitive  verbs
line=221 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,366.31,538.62,380.3 iscore=0.00                                                                  :The examples  in (12) illustrate some of the prefixes from the POSS, AGT and PAT set.
line=222 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,350.18,538.62,364.16 iscore=0.12                                                                         :Note that (12b) realizes a direct setting, and (12c) an inverse setting. (12d) shows an
line=223 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,334.1,538.62,348.08 iscore=0.20                                                                          :example  with an inverse setting because the more proximate (more  salient) demon-
line=224 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,318.02,538.55,332.0 iscore=0.17                                                                          :strative appears with the lower argument. With ditransitive verbs, the theme argument
line=225 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,301.94,538.55,315.92 iscore=0.13                                                                         :can be incorporated so that a transitive pattern results, and the recipient in (12e) is
line=226 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,285.79,538.69,299.78 iscore=0.25                                                                 :marked  with the PAT prefix because it is higher on the person scale. If both arguments
line=227 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,269.72,447.56,283.7 iscore=0.19                                                                          :are 1st or 2nd person, a portmanteau prefix is used, as shown in (12f).
