line=397 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,462.5,538.61,476.48 iscore=0.00                                                                   :The introduction of a direct vs. inverse marker seems to be an ingenious invention to
line=398 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,446.42,538.49,460.4 iscore=0.33                                                                   :solve the problem raised in the beginning, namely to mark an inverse setting differ-
line=399 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,430.34,538.6,444.32 iscore=0.21                                                                   :ently from a direct setting. However, this invention brings also some disadvantages,
line=400 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,414.2,315.0,428.18 iscore=0.08                                                                    :as well as other complexities for computation.
line=401 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,397.22,538.65,411.2 iscore=0.15                                                                  :   First, salience must be made explicit in every transitive setting, which might be
line=402 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,380.12,538.62,394.1 iscore=0.27                                                                   :seen as a disadvantage. In the settings 1→2 and 2→1 both persons, being speech act
line=403 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,363.08,538.59,377.06 iscore=0.13                                                                  :participants, are salient. Some languages, as we have seen above, use portmanteau
line=404 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,346.04,538.63,360.02 iscore=0.17                                                                  :morphemes   under this condition. The Algonquian languages have arbitrarily set the
line=405 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,329.06,538.59,343.04 iscore=0.12                                                                  :2nd person to be more salient than the 1st person, and a further pair of direct/inverse
line=406 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,312.08,538.57,326.06 iscore=0.06                                                                  :voice markers dealing with 1,2-settings has been introduced. Furthermore, in the set-
line=407 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,294.92,538.65,308.9 iscore=0.14                                                                   :ting 3→3 (where  both arguments are human or animate), one argument must be more
line=408 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,277.94,538.62,291.92 iscore=0.14                                                                  :salient than the other one, for instance in terms of discourse prominence. Here, the
line=409 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,260.78,538.64,274.76 iscore=0.21                                                                  :less salient argument is marked by obviative, so that 3→3obv and 3obv→3  can be
line=410 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,243.74,538.62,257.72 iscore=0.29                                                                  :distinguished. (21) illustrates the marking of local person in Plains Cree, and (22) the
line=411 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,226.64,203.08,240.62 iscore=0.07                                                                  :marking of 3→3   settings.
line=412 tag=M+AC+LN+CN span_id=101-20 lang_name=Plains Cree lang_code=crk fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,204.5,245.27,218.48 iscore=0.33 :(21)  Local person in Plains Cree
