line=427 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,642.68,538.53,656.66 iscore=0.14                                                                      :Note that with obviative marking on the dependent  noun, either the higher or the
line=428 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,625.7,538.63,639.68 iscore=0.29                                                                       :lower argument can be marked  as obviative, given that both arguments are animate.
line=429 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,608.72,538.7,622.7 iscore=0.06                                                                        :This raises the number of possible forms to four rather than two, which reminds at the
line=430 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,591.68,259.49,605.66 iscore=0.19                                                                      :situation in a language with passive.
line=431 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=84.12,574.58,538.62,588.56 iscore=0.08                                                                     :     In (23) the two settings 3→3obv and 3obv→3 are illustrated, the former realized
line=432 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,557.54,378.13,571.52 iscore=0.23                                                                      :by the direct marker, and the latter by the inverse marker.
line=433 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,535.46,341.93,549.44 iscore=0.09                                                              :(23)       direct setting         inverse setting
line=434 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0,F3-14.0 bbox=124.68,518.35,374.8,532.34 iscore=0.50                                                     :           λy    λx  VERB(x,y)    λy   λx  VERB(x,y)
line=435 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=124.69,502.22,311.15,516.2 iscore=0.67                                                                     :           +hr   +lr              +hr  +lr
line=436 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=124.73,486.08,322.7,500.06 iscore=0.50                                                                     :           3obv   3                3   3obv
line=437 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=124.7,470.0,315.03,483.98 iscore=0.50                                                                      :           +hs                         +hs
line=438 fonts=F1-11.0 bbox=128.16,453.91,314.02,464.89 iscore=0.00                                                                    :            DIRECT                 INVERSE
line=439 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,430.94,538.64,444.92 iscore=0.00                                                                      :The reference to person (rather than abstract case) also has computational advantages
line=440 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,413.9,538.64,427.88 iscore=0.17                                                                       :beyond  argument linking; it allows reference-tracking across clause boundaries (es-
line=441 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,396.92,538.51,410.9 iscore=0.25                                                                       :pecially when obviative marking is involved). Consider the examples in (24), where
line=442 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,379.94,538.61,393.92 iscore=0.19                                                                      :the dependent verb in the conjunct mood can be marked for obviative; in this case it
line=443 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,362.9,538.64,376.88 iscore=0.12                                                                       :is interpreted as coindexed with the less salient (obviative) argument in the main
line=444 fonts=F1-14.0,F1-9.0 bbox=56.7,345.92,538.6,361.4 iscore=0.15                                                                 :clause, otherwise it is coindexed with the more salient (proximate) argument.^{3} (Such
line=445 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,328.94,460.63,342.92 iscore=0.33                                                                      :a device could be reinterpreted as ‘same subject’ vs. ‘different subject’.)

doc_id=101 page=12 block_id=12-3 bbox=56.7,59.29,538.63,257.06 label=b 446 460
line=446 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-7.0 bbox=56.7,245.05,538.61,257.06                                                                  :3   Similar devices for the marking of discourse prominence have been developed in other languages, too.
line=447 fonts=F1-11.0 bbox=73.68,232.09,538.62,243.07 iscore=0.27                                                            :    Navajo (an Athabascan  language exhibiting accusative in pronominal affixes) not only can mark a so-
line=448 fonts=F1-11.0 bbox=73.68,219.07,538.63,230.05 iscore=0.12                                                            :    called 4th person as the least prominent 3rd person, but also distinguishes whether a 3rd person object
line=449 fonts=F1-11.0,F2-11.0 bbox=73.68,206.05,538.61,217.03 iscore=0.29                                                    :    (including possessors) is less prominent than a 3rd person subject (marked by the prefix yi-) or more
line=450 fonts=F1-11.0,F2-11.0 bbox=73.68,193.09,333.24,204.07 iscore=0.12                                                    :    prominent (marked by bi-) (Thompson  1996, Willie 2000).
line=451 tag=L span_id=101-26 lang_name=Navajo lang_code=nav fonts=F1-11.0,F5-11.0 bbox=73.68,180.31,224.26,191.29 iscore=0.25:    (i) a. líí    dzaanééz   yi-zta¬.
