line=479 fonts=F1-14.0,F1-16.0 bbox=56.7,450.26,538.6,466.28              :2.6   Generalized   case type: Affixes on the verb, as well as morphological cases
line=480 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,433.28,538.59,447.26 iscore=0.23         :on the complement,  encode  argument hierarchy. It is also possible to encode argu-
line=481 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,416.3,538.61,430.28 iscore=0.20          :ment hierarchy in the context of salience values (split case). This type might be seen
line=482 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,399.26,538.65,413.24 iscore=0.20         :as the most effective type because it is structurally determined but does not need to
line=483 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,382.28,538.62,396.26 iscore=0.20         :map  hierarchies onto each other, as in the inverse type. The notion ‘generalized case’
line=484 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,365.3,538.66,379.28 iscore=0.14          :subsumes  morphological case and  pronominal affixes (as well as agreement morph-
line=485 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,348.26,437.89,362.24 iscore=0.36         :emes), which in many respects behave similarly, under one concept.
line=486 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,331.28,538.7,345.26 iscore=0.10         :   In Lexical Decomposition  Grammar   (LDG),  argument  hierarchy is encoded  by
line=487 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,314.3,538.59,328.28 iscore=0.00          :means  of two  relational features associated with the theta-roles: [+hr] ‘there is a
line=488 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,297.26,538.61,311.24 iscore=0.19         :higher role’, and [+lr] ‘there is a lower role’. These features are either based on the
line=489 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,280.28,538.64,294.26 iscore=0.31         :semantic hierarchy of arguments (in the unmarked  case, corresponding to the cano-
line=490 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,263.3,538.62,277.28 iscore=0.25          :nical realization of arguments), or they are assigned lexically (‘lexical case’). (Wun-
line=491 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,246.26,225.16,260.24 iscore=0.08         :derlich 1997, Stiebels 2000b.)
line=492 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,229.28,538.59,243.26 iscore=0.00        :   Pronominal  affixes or clitics as well as morphological case are specified by the
line=493 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,212.3,179.71,226.28 iscore=0.00          :same type of features:
line=494 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,189.98,222.33,203.96 iscore=0.40         :(25)  Linker features in LDG
line=495 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,173.89,228.28,187.88 iscore=0.50:      [+hr,+lr]  dative (DAT)
line=496 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,157.81,375.59,171.8 iscore=0.33 :      [+hr]      accusative (ACC) (genitive with nouns)
line=497 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,141.67,241.0,155.66 iscore=0.33 :      [+lr]      ergative (ERG)
line=498 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,125.59,260.08,139.58 iscore=0.50:      [ ]        nominative (NOM)
line=499 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,103.52,538.61,117.5 iscore=0.08          :These four linkers together form a complete lattice. Therefore, the prediction is that
line=500 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,87.44,538.6,101.42 iscore=0.23           :no other structural linkers can exist, except those that have additional semantic feat-
line=501 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,71.3,538.69,85.28 iscore=0.19            :ures (such as partitive). The main difference to the way in which the positional type is

