line=503 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,758.18,538.64,772.16                              :characterized comes from  the feature [+lr], which encodes the argument hierarchy
line=504 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,741.08,538.57,755.06 iscore=0.14                  :under a reversed perspective: while the feature value [−hr] singles out the highest ar-
line=505 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,723.92,538.59,737.9 iscore=0.21                   :gument  as a designated argument (‘subject’), the feature value [−lr] singles out the
line=506 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,707.78,538.56,721.76 iscore=0.15                  :lowest argument  as designated (‘direct object’), in contrast to the positional type,
line=507 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,691.7,538.61,705.68 iscore=0.08                   :where the second-to-highest argument is designated (‘primary object’). Moreover, the
line=508 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,675.62,538.59,689.6 iscore=0.15                   :fact that both the underlying argument roles and the morphological items are speci-
line=509 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,659.48,538.67,673.46 iscore=0.23                  :fied by  the same  features makes  a correspondence-theoretic analysis promising
line=510 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,643.4,183.88,657.38 iscore=0.10                   :(Wunderlich 2001a,b).
line=511 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,626.6,538.6,640.58 iscore=0.00                   :   Generalized case is a purely structural device, independent of semantic role. (26)
line=512 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,609.56,538.63,623.54 iscore=0.08                  :shows  that canonical argument linking makes no  difference between agentive and
line=513 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,592.58,538.6,606.56 iscore=0.17                   :non-agentive verbs; only the number of arguments is relevant. All intransitive verbs
line=514 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,575.59,538.61,589.58 iscore=0.08          :have a NOM  argument, whereas  transitive verbs show either the NOM-ACC pattern or
line=515 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,558.55,538.68,572.54 iscore=0.08          :the ERG-NOM  pattern (depending on typological parameters). Under certain circum-
line=516 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,541.57,538.61,555.56 iscore=0.13          :stances, ERG-ACC is possible, but in this case a direct contrast to the default case
line=517 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,524.59,538.62,538.58 iscore=0.13          :(NOM)  is lacking. Similarly, ditransitive verbs show either the NOM-DAT-ACC pattern
line=518 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,507.55,217.77,521.54 iscore=0.09          :or the ERG-DAT-NOM  pattern.
