line=545 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,758.18,538.55,772.16                            :   There is a fundamental semantic asymmetry between  the arguments of a transitive
line=546 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,742.1,538.59,756.08 iscore=0.14                  :verb: The direct setting is more natural than the inverse setting because local persons
line=547 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,726.02,538.65,740.0 iscore=0.21                  :(1st or 2nd) tend to be agent. Similarly, the highest argument (the logical subject)
line=548 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,709.88,538.6,723.86 iscore=0.14                  :ranks above the lower  arguments (logical objects) because agents, who control the
line=549 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,693.8,538.57,707.78 iscore=0.15                  :event denoted by a verb, are mostly in highest position. These asymmetries influence
line=550 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,677.72,538.62,691.7 iscore=0.15                  :morphological  realization: what has to be marked is the more  unnatural situation
line=551 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,661.58,538.61,675.56 iscore=0.13                 :rather than the more natural one. Therefore, the inverse setting is more likely to be
line=552 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,645.5,538.59,659.48 iscore=0.07                  :marked  morphologically than the direct setting. Similarly, highest arguments that are
line=553 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,629.42,538.58,643.4 iscore=0.28                  :not agents or not 1st or 2nd person are more likely to be marked than those that are
line=554 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,613.34,211.43,627.32 iscore=0.06                 :agents or 1st or 2nd person.
line=555 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,597.2,538.62,611.18 iscore=0.00                 :   Following Stiebels (2000a,b), I assume the two scales in (27a); the first concerns
line=556 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,581.12,538.54,595.1 iscore=0.31                  :the relation between meaning and morphosyntax, while the second is a pure semantic
line=557 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,565.04,538.64,579.02 iscore=0.23                 :relation. Harmonic alignment then yields the contextualized preferences expressed in
line=558 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,548.9,460.92,562.88 iscore=0.18                  :(27b), which in turn give the markedness hierarchies expressed in (27c).
line=559 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,526.82,321.25,540.8 iscore=0.18                  :(27)  Harmonic  alignment for generalized case
line=560 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,510.74,517.8,524.72 iscore=0.33                 :      a. +hr  > +lr       Morphological marking  by [+hr] is more effective than
line=561 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=209.7,494.6,280.82,508.58 iscore=0.12                 :                          that by [+lr].
line=562 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=107.7,477.5,356.34,491.48 iscore=0.25                 :         +loc >  −loc     Person hierarchy (1,2 > 3)
line=563 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,455.36,309.71,469.34 iscore=0.25                :      b. Case in the context of person values
line=564 fonts=F1-14.0,F9-14.0 bbox=107.7,438.26,222.46,452.24 iscore=0.29        :         +hr/+loc n +hr/−loc
line=565 fonts=F1-14.0,F9-14.0 bbox=107.7,421.1,219.71,435.08 iscore=1.00         :         +lr/−loc n +lr/+loc
line=566 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,398.96,240.23,412.94 iscore=0.67                :      c. Markedness hierarchies
line=567 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=107.7,381.85,483.1,395.84 iscore=0.18         :         *(+hr)/−loc » *(+hr)/+loc   ACC for a 3rd person is more marked
line=568 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=277.68,365.71,501.65,379.7 iscore=0.25        :                                     (less likely) than ACC for the 1st person.
line=569 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=107.7,348.61,491.05,362.6 iscore=0.18         :         *(+lr)/+loc » *(+lr)/−loc   ERG for the 1st person is more marked
line=570 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=277.68,332.47,492.49,346.46 iscore=0.38       :                                     (less likely) than ERG for a 3rd person.
line=571 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,310.4,538.66,324.38 iscore=0.09                  :These  markedness  hierarchies explain the phenomenon of split case, depending on
line=572 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,294.26,538.59,308.24 iscore=0.19                 :salience in terms of person. The split case type thus reflects the fact that only inverse
line=573 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,278.18,195.64,292.16 iscore=0.12                 :settings must be marked.
line=574 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,256.1,161.67,270.08 iscore=0.25                  :(28)     Split case
line=575 fonts=F2-14.0 bbox=107.7,239.84,466.01,253.82 iscore=0.20                :         direct setting        inverse setting           intransitives
