line=644 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,395.12,538.65,409.1 iscore=0.00                  :Note that the four instances of lexical marking are described by just two features,
line=645 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,379.04,538.57,393.02 iscore=0.07                 :which, moreover, are identical to the features independently used, but associated with
line=646 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,362.9,538.61,376.88 iscore=0.14                  :(possible) semantic information. This account is enabled by the fact that dative is de-
line=647 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,346.82,538.62,360.8 iscore=0.27                  :composed  into two features ([+hr,+lr]); it is more general, and at the same time more
line=648 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,330.74,353.63,344.72 iscore=0.07                 :explanative than simply stipulating ‘dative’ marking.
line=649 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,308.66,182.7,322.64 iscore=0.17                  :(32)  Lexical marking
line=650 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,292.58,529.7,306.56 iscore=0.07                 :      a. Lexical dative is induced by [+lr] or [+hr], depending on the position of the
line=651 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=108.54,276.5,210.19,290.48 iscore=0.14                :         marked argument.
line=652 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,260.41,528.1,274.4 iscore=0.13          :      b. Lexical marking by [+hr] leads to DAT or ACC, depending on the number of
line=653 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=108.54,244.34,170.28,258.32 iscore=0.07               :         arguments.
line=654 fonts=F1-11.0,F1-14.0 bbox=90.72,228.25,524.38,242.24 iscore=0.07        :      c. Lexical marking by [+lr] leads to DAT or ERG, depending on the number of
line=655 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=108.54,212.18,170.28,226.16 iscore=0.07               :         arguments.
line=656 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,189.2,538.54,203.18 iscore=0.06                  :There is, of course, much more  to say about generalized case. One point to be re-
line=657 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,172.16,538.55,186.14 iscore=0.06                 :peated here is the fact that languages belonging to this type, which clearly are the ma-
line=658 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,155.18,538.64,169.16 iscore=0.19                 :jority of languages, can identify the arguments on the head (by pronominal affixes,
line=659 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,138.2,538.6,152.18 iscore=0.46                   :clitics or agreement morphemes) or on the complement  (by morphological case), or
line=660 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,121.16,538.64,135.14 iscore=0.25                 :on both. Morphological case is interesting because it presupposes a strong syntactic
line=661 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,104.18,538.64,118.16 iscore=0.25                 :relation between head and complement.  By  contrast, coindexation by head-marking
line=662 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,87.2,538.64,101.18 iscore=0.25                   :only requires the weaker  adjunct relation between nominals and  the verbal head.

