line=664 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,757.28,538.69,771.26                                                                                  :Thus, the generalized case type is the only argument linking type which successfully
line=665 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,740.3,331.54,754.28 iscore=0.08                                                                       :bridges the gap between morphology and syntax.
line=666 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,723.32,538.65,737.3 iscore=0.00                                                                      :   Moreover, the possibility of having simultaneously head-marking and morpholo-
line=667 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,706.28,538.61,720.26 iscore=0.20                                                                      :gical case allows various kinds of split. For instance, head-marking can be of the ac-
line=668 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,689.3,538.64,703.28 iscore=0.07                                                                       :cusative type, while morphological case is ergative-based (an example is Kalkatungu,
line=669 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,672.32,538.68,686.3 iscore=0.15                                                                       :see Blake 1994). Or, as one finds in Austronesian languages, head-marking can be
line=670 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,655.28,538.61,669.26 iscore=0.23                                                                      :based on argument hierarchy, while morphological case depends on discourse promi-
line=671 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,638.3,538.64,652.28 iscore=0.25                                                                       :nence. Consider the following examples from Tukang Besi, spoken on some  islands
line=672 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,621.32,538.56,635.3 iscore=0.17                                                                       :of Indonesia (Donohue 1999); here, the accusative agreement morpheme is only real-
line=673 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,604.28,538.65,618.26 iscore=0.18                                                                      :ized on the verb if the object is the more prominent argument, to be marked by nomi-
line=674 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,587.3,538.62,601.28 iscore=0.29                                                               :native case. (The less prominent argument is marked by the case particle te, which
line=675 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,570.32,538.65,584.3 iscore=0.21                                                                       :differs from oblique marking in adjuncts; the default syntactic ordering is VOS; only
line=676 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,553.28,361.62,567.26 iscore=0.15                                                                      :nominative arguments can be deleted in coordination.)
line=677 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,530.48,516.79,544.46 iscore=0.15                                                                      :(33)  Coreference with the most prominent argument of the first clause in Tukang
