line=688 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,312.08,538.63,326.06             :I have argued in this paper that argument linking depends on three factors: semantic
line=689 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,295.1,538.63,309.08 iscore=0.14  :role (by which semantic classes of verbs can be distinguished), salience (by which
line=690 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,278.06,538.7,292.04 iscore=0.23  :semantic properties of the arguments themselves are taken into account), and argu-
line=691 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,261.08,538.58,275.06 iscore=0.17 :ment  hierarchy (which distinguishes positions in a complex predicate). Four of the
line=692 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,244.1,538.64,258.08 iscore=0.23  :types discussed here are mainly realized by morphological means: one type uses se-
line=693 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,227.06,538.55,241.04 iscore=0.40 :mantic role, another type uses salience, and a third type, the inverse type, encodes the
line=694 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,210.08,538.6,224.06 iscore=0.07  :difference between direct and inverse settings directly by mapping relative salience
line=695 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,193.1,538.51,207.08 iscore=0.23  :onto argument hierarchy. The fourth type, the portmanteau type, consists in the pure
line=696 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,176.06,538.57,190.04 iscore=0.15 :listing of combinations of salience and argument positions, and thus does not allow
line=697 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,159.08,538.65,173.06 iscore=0.29 :any generalizations. It would be interesting to speculate on how this type may have
line=698 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,142.1,117.7,156.08 iscore=0.07   :developed.
line=699 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,125.06,538.61,139.04 iscore=0.00:   In contrast, the positional type only uses syntactic means, and the generalized case
line=700 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,108.08,538.58,122.06 iscore=0.23 :type, although overwhelmingly also of morphological nature, in some of its subtypes
line=701 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,91.1,538.67,105.08 iscore=0.38   :presupposes a strong syntactic relation. Moreover, this type also has variants in which

