line=703 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,757.46,538.55,771.44                   :semantic role and salience are encoded; so it turns out to be most effective type. (34)
line=704 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,740.48,295.07,754.46 iscore=0.12       :summarizes  these findings in an overview.
line=705 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,718.22,293.62,732.2 iscore=0.33        :(34)  Overview  of argument linking types
line=706 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=121.92,701.6,508.69,715.58 iscore=0.00      :           Semantic role      Salience     Argument  hierarchy       Domain
line=707 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=87.18,685.04,319.54,699.02 iscore=0.00      :     1                      Portmanteau  type
line=708 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=87.18,662.9,521.19,682.4 iscore=0.25        :     2      Active type                                            Morphology
line=709 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=87.18,635.24,356.91,649.22 iscore=0.25      :     5                                 Inverse type
line=710 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=87.18,618.62,533.09,632.6 iscore=0.17       :     6                                    Generalized case type  Morphology  and
line=711 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=114.54,602.0,505.6,616.52 iscore=0.00       :          Lexical marking    Case split                               Syntax
line=712 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=87.18,585.44,505.61,599.42 iscore=0.20      :     4                                       Positional type          Syntax
line=713 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,562.1,538.54,576.08 iscore=0.00        :Some  of these types also developed means  to encode  discourse prominence  in set-
line=714 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,545.12,538.63,559.1 iscore=0.29        :tings with 3rd persons that are sortally alike, and thus allow reference tracking across
line=715 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,528.08,538.65,542.06 iscore=0.07       :clause boundaries. It seems that, at least in some instances, these means are taken
line=716 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,511.1,538.61,525.08 iscore=0.21        :from the argument  linking device and then reinterpreted. In particular, devices that
line=717 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,494.12,538.61,508.1 iscore=0.25        :use argument  hierarchy can be  reinterpreted with regard to prominence hierarchy.
line=718 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,477.08,538.5,491.06 iscore=0.38        :This indicates that the encoding of discourse prominence is a secondary purpose of
line=719 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,460.1,538.58,474.08 iscore=0.15        :grammar,  interacting with an already existing system of argument linking. As illus-
line=720 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,443.12,538.61,457.1 iscore=0.21        :trated above, the inverse type, the positional type and the generalized case type have
line=721 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,426.08,538.59,440.06 iscore=0.29       :incorporated effective means of encoding discourse prominence. However,  this topic
line=722 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,409.1,305.62,423.08 iscore=0.20        :clearly deserves more detailed investigation.
line=723 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=73.68,392.12,538.62,406.1 iscore=0.00       :   One  may speculate about what may  have  prompted the evolution of so many dif-
line=724 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,375.08,538.52,389.06 iscore=0.14       :ferent types of argument linking. Why are the purely morphological types only found
line=725 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,358.1,538.66,372.08 iscore=0.20        :in languages of small populations and have never been  created in other parts of the
line=726 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,341.12,538.59,355.1 iscore=0.20        :world? Are  these types in any sense defective? Had the populations that speak these
line=727 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,324.08,538.61,338.06 iscore=0.36       :languages never  the chance to incorporate the notion of abstract case? It has been
line=728 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,307.1,538.62,321.08 iscore=0.20        :shown  that even the positional type and the generalized case type differ in one impor-
line=729 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,290.12,538.62,304.1 iscore=0.27        :tant aspect: they lead to different options for the designated object, which is either the
line=730 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,273.08,538.64,287.06 iscore=0.27       :second-to-highest argument  (‘primary object’) or the lowest argument  (‘direct ob-
line=731 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,256.1,538.67,270.08 iscore=0.15        :ject’). This variety of types makes it difficult to assume that Universal Grammar
line=732 fonts=F1-14.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.7,239.12,538.56,253.1 iscore=0.21:(UG), created in the evolution of homo sapiens, already incorporated the idea of ab-
line=733 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,222.08,538.6,236.06 iscore=0.29        :stract case. However, what we can assume to be part of UG are the main factors out-
line=734 fonts=F1-14.0 bbox=56.7,205.1,538.64,219.08 iscore=0.29        :lined here (semantic role, salience, and argument hierarchy), which are differently
